This value added catalog provides updated redshift and classification information for optical counterparts to X-ray sources detected in the <a href="https://www.mpe.mpg.de/eROSITA">eROSITA</a> Final Equatorial Depth Survey (<a href="https://www.sdss.org/dr18/bhm/programs/spiders/">eFEDS</a>) field (<a href="https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2022A&A...661A...1B">Brunner et al., 2022</a>, <a href="https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2022A&A...661A...3S">Salvato et al., 2022</a>). We updated the spectroscopic redshift and classifications (w.r.t. Salvato et al. 2022), using a large spectroscopic compilation, derived from several facilities, but dominated by SDSS optical spectroscopy. We included new information derived from 37 dedicated SDSS-V plates, observed between December 2020 and May 2021. We combined automated redshift and classifications, derived from the <a href="https://www.sdss.org/dr18/software/pipelines/boss/">standard SDSS idlspec1d pipeline</a>, with an extensive and targeted set of visual inspections, which increase the reliability and completeness of the spectroscopic coverage. 

We provide three files:
i) eFEDS_Main_speccomp - an update of redshift/classification information for the eFEDS Main (0.2-2.3keV selection) source counterparts catalogue;
ii) eFEDS_Hard_speccomp - an update of redshift/classification information for the eFEDS Hard band (2.3-5keV selection) source counterparts catalogue; 
iii) eFEDS_SDSSV_spec_results - a catalogue of spectroscopic redshifts and classifications derived solely from the SDSS-V/eFEDS plate data set, supplemented by the results of an extensive visual inspection process. 

A full description of this value added catalog will be provided in Merloni et al. (in prep).
